the new sesquipedalian blog archive python pyphon in p&p meeting the new sesquipedalian the stanford linguistics newsletter department events calendar archive subscribe python pyphon in p&p meeting ed king writes this friday sam bowman will be giving a tutorial on pyphon a set of python libraries for working with ot and hg grammars sam's abstract follows also note that we have a room change since semfest will be stealing the greenberg room on friday our new room is 460 334 on the third floor of margaret jacks at the usual time 12 noon tutorial building ot grammars in pyphon i will be giving an introduction to pyphon a powerful open source software suite for working with optimality theory which was developed by jason riggle and max bane and which i have recently been contributing to to quote the documentation pyphon currently offers the following functionality state your model as a set of hand crafted tableaux as in otsoft or ot help or simply specify your constraints as regular expressions and let full tableaux be computed automatically for any input forms tableaux candidates can be generated for either ot or hg produce finite state diagrams of your regular constraints generate optima and or typologies in both ot and hg optionally subject to grammatical restrictions that can be specified in a variety of ways as stratified hierarchies ot as partial orders ot as sets of elementary ranking conditions ot as sets of weight assignments and or inequalities hg count the number of rankings ot or volume of weightings hg that generate each output form compute typological implications t orders a la anttila and andrus 2006 and render pretty graphs create and search typologies in cyclic ot and two tiered lpm ot after kiparsky 2000 it is a work in progress and some functions including stratal ot are not yet fully implemented but your comments may help to steer its short term development sesquipedalian issue 2012 03 16 events grads groups johnston talk on consciousness search for i